mkdir scripts data
cd scripts/

~/sharedscratch/cgebm_pipelines_test/enrichment_ppln.sh
usage: enrichment_ppln.sh -t <TT_XLSX> -s <SYMBOL_COL> -f <LFC_COL> -F <LFC_THRESH> \
      -q <PADJ_COL> -Q <FDR_THRESH> -r <RANKING_COL> -v <MIN_OVLP> -C <MSIG_CATS_STR> \
      -o <ORG_NAME> -O <ENR_PDF> -h
---
-t  path to a .xlsx file with tabs named *_gene_table. Each tab contains a ranked table of genes.
    Columns will contain gene symbols and one or more ranking statistics such as log fold change
    and p-value or false discovery rate.
    [obligatory]
-s  Name of symbol column in .xlsx file.
    [default: symbol]
-f  Name of log fold change column in .xlsx file. Used for thresholding gene significance.
    [default: logFC]
-F  Absolute log2 fold change threshold, part of detection of gene significance for eventual
    gene list enrichment analysis.
    [default: 0.0]
-q  Column name in .xlsx file where estimates of FDR (Q-values) are found.
    [default: padj]
-Q  FDR threshold. Numeric significance threshold for gene differential expression.
    [default: 0.05]
-r  Name of gene ranking column in .xlsx file. Used for GSEA analysis. Rarely, if too few genes are
    up or down, this ranking will be used to choose 100 genes for list enrichment. If no ranking
    column is specified, no GSEA analysis will be performed and list enrichment will be skipped if
    there are fewer than the minimum number of genes required for overlaps (see -v option)
    [default: no ranking column]
-v  Minimum number of overlaps between genes deemed significant and a gene category list.
    [default: 3]
-C  Comma-separated specifiers of collections within the Molecular Signatures Database to use in
    enrichment analyses (see https://www.gsea-msigdb.org/gsea/msigdb):
    [default: "C2,C5,H"]
-o  Organism name: one of human, mouse, Xlaevis, Xtropicalis, Calbicans, rice.
    This sets various variables/libraries. Ask for others.
    [obligatory]
-O  path to enrichment pdf. Provide a stub name with .pdf extension. This will be modified with
    an extension reflecting each enrichment result.
    [default: ../results/enrichmnet/enr_.pdf]
-h  print this help message.
ERROR: obligatory data file argument (-t) missing
ERROR: obligatory data file  not found
ERROR: obligatory organism name (-o) not specified

